Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.94,0:26:14.69,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其名字平淡无奇 HS1946+7658\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which has the prosaic-sounding name HS1946+7658.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.73,0:26:17.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,为何我会说它就是最大的黑洞呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why do l say it's the largest black hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.36,0:26:19.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为我们知道它是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because we know it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.28,0:26:23.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,目前为止所发现的宇宙间最亮的类星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most luminous quasar in the universe...that's been found so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.70,0:26:25.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,黑洞将其牢牢掌握\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The black hole that's holding it together...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.50,0:26:31.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其产生的能量需要太阳质量的约100亿倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's producing the energy...needs to be about 10 billion times...the mass of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.13,0:26:37.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相当于黑洞要比我们整个太阳系还大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That corresponds to a black hole...which is larger than our entire solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.88,0:26:43.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 它在那里提醒着我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, it'sjust out there to remind us how bizarre...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.35,0:26:48.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个看似简单的引力居然会有这么怪异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a seemingly simple force like gravity can actually be.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.85,0:26:50.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最大的超大质量黑洞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The largest supermassive black hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.90,0:26:54.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在星系中央掌控大权\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wields power in the center of a galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.40,0:26:57.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不过在宇宙间还有其它的大发光体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but there are other big luminous objects...in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.69,0:27:05.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上 我们环顾四周 似乎还存在着某些东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln fact, there are some that seem to exist...everywhere we look.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.58,0:27:07.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当我们扫视夜空时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we glance into the nighttime sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.79,0:27:10.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,看到星星 闪烁着星光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we see stars, twinkling dots of light...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.58,0:27:15.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那实际上是发光的等离子球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are actually luminous balls of plasma.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.42,0:27:17.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尽管从地球上看 它们很小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although they may seem small from Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.71,0:27:21.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而星星有各种各样的个头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stars come in a variety of sizes...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.05,0:27:25.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从红矮星 我们太阳质量的1/12\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from red dwarfs...which are about1/12 the mass of our sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.72,0:27:27.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,到蓝白超级巨星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to blue-white super giants...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.68,0:27:33.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,可以达到太阳质量的150倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can get as big as 150 solar masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.98,0:27:37.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们银河系里有1亿颗恒星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Milky Way holds 100 billion stars...
